text: The following is a list of languages used in Ireland: *Irish English - the dialects of the English language spoken in the Ireland *Scots - is the dialect of English spoken in much of Scotland and Ireland. *British English - the dialects of the English language spoken in the United Kingdom *Ulster Scots - the dialects of the Scots spoken in Northern Ireland *Irish Gaelic - the Gaelic (language) spoken in parts of Ireland *English language - the English language spoken worldwide *Ulster Irish - the dialects of the Irish Gaelic spoken in Northern Ireland *Ulster English - the dialects of the Irish English and British English spoken in Northern Ireland Category:Language-related lists
title: Languages of Ireland
